20generated%20%248.7%20billion%20in%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20expect%20anyone%20to%20hold%20a%20parade%20to%20honor%20Netflix's%20achievement.%20Wall%20Street%20expects%20this%20kind%20of%20performance%20from%20Netflix%2C%20which%20is%20why%20its%20stock%20is%20near%20an%20all-time%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20still%20worth%20noting%20because%20not%20very%20long%20ago%2C%20lots%20of%20very%20reasonable%20people%20thought%20Netflix%20might%20never%20get%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20Netflix%20used%20to%20be%20in%20the%20business%20of%20burning%20cash%20%E2%80%94%20billions%20of%20dollars%20worth%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20as%20it%20built%20a%20lead%20in%20the%20streaming%20wars%20by%20licensing%20other%20people's%20TV%20shows%20and%20movies%2C%20and%20making%20its%20own.%20And%20Netflix%20financed%20all%20that%20cash%20incineration%20by%20taking%20on%20many%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%202020%2C%20the%20company%20had%20more%20than%20%2415%20billion%20in%20long-term%20debt%2C%20and%20a%20concern%20you%20heard%20all%20the%20time%20from%20Netflix%20bears%20was%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20great%20that%20they're%20spending%20all%20this%20money%20on%20content%2C%20but%20when%20are%20they%20going%20to%20pay%20for%20it%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Netflix%20answer%20went%20something%20like%3A%20%26quot%3BTrust%20us%3A%20All%20the%20money%20we%20spend%20on%20content%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20content%20we%20own%2C%20forever%20%E2%80%94%20is%20money%20well-spent%20because%20it%20means%20we%20can%20attract%20more%20customers%2C%20who%20will%20give%20us%20more%20money.%20And%20eventually%2C%20we'll%20have%20so%20many%20customers%2C%20and%20so%20much%20money%2C%20that%20we%20won't%20have%20to%20borrow%20any%20more%20to%20keep%20this%20going.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20they%20pulled%20it%20off%3A%20In%20January%202021%2C%20Netflix%20said%20it%20no%20longer%20had%20to%20tap%20the%20debt%20market%20