ears%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20about%20his%20appointments%20to%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20during%20an%20interview%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20follow%2C%20no%20index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FHlWT6nYZ4OU%3Fsi%3D0oOMlQYMf3jPUIOa%26t%3D2140%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20get%20none.%20Because%2C%20you%20know%2C%20you%20put%20them%20in%2C%20they're%20young.%20You%20tend%20to%20put%20them%20in%20young.%26quot%3B%20He%20continued%20on%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BOnly%20stupid%20people%20put%20old.%20You%20know%2C%20you%20don't%20put%20old%20in%2C%20because%20they're%20there%20for%20two%20years%20or%20three%20years%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20Supreme%20Court%20appointments%2C%20including%20Neil%20Gorsuch%2C%20Brett%20Kavanaugh%2C%20and%20Amy%20Coney%20Barrett%2C%20skewed%20younger%20than%20typical%2C%20with%20an%20average%20age%20of%2050%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20historical%20average%20of%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20Supreme%20Court%20appointees%20of%20President%20Trump%20have%20significantly%20contributed%20to%20the%20conservative%20majority%20in%20the%20court%2C%20leading%20to%20notable%20changes%20in%20federal%20precedents.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20outcomes%20of%20this%20shift%20is%20the%20overturning%20of%20Roe%20vs%20Wade%2C%20a%20landmark%20ruling%20that%20previously%20protected%20the%20right%20to%20abortion%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20interviewer%20called%20attention%20to%20his%20age%20being%2078%2C%20Trump%20brushed%20off%20the%20question%20and%20continued%20to%20talk%20about%20his%20Supreme%20Court%20appointees%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20I%20got%20three%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20responded.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20presidents%20get%20none%2C%20I%20got%20three.%20And%2C%20uh%2C%20I%20think%20they've%20been%20three%20great%20choices%20too%2C%20by%20the%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20questions%20raised%20about%20Trump's%20mental%20fitness%20for%20the%20office%20since%20he%20has%20gone%20on%20long%20frequent%20rambles%20at%20rallies%2C%20ignored%20or%20missed%20questions%20and%20recently%2C%20spent%20time%20swaying%20at%20a%20town%20hall%20instead%20of%20answering%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Ben%20Michaelis%2C%20a%20clinical%20psychologist%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20follow%2C%20no%20index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fus-politics%2Ftrump-mental-health-fears-cognitive-decline-b2625124.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Independent%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Trump%20is%20%26quot%3Breally%20not%20in%20a%20strong%20cognitive%20place.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20term%20when%20you're%20talking%20about%20people%20with%20dementia%20called%20sundowning%2C%20it's%20a%20lot%20harder%20for%20them%20as%20the%20day%20goes%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20maintain%20focus%20on%20a%20topic.%20The%20idea%20of%20being%20able%20to%20maintain%20that%20level%20of%20focus%20for%20that%20amount%20of%20time%2C%20that%20late%20in%20the%20day...you%20wouldn't%20think%20twice%20about%20it%20if%20that%20was%20your%20grandfather.%20It's%20just%20he%20happens%20to%20be%20running%20for%20president.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729202700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Ff41du9is_donald-trump-afp_625x300_18_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-oldest-to-run-for-president-says-only-stupid-people-put-old-in-6813745%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20has%20said%20%26quot%3Bonly%20stupid%20people%20put%20old%20people%26quot%3B%20in%20positions%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20-%20ironically%20letting%20slip%20that%20he%20himself%20is%20a%2078-year-old%20running%20for%20the%20highest%20office%20in%20the%20US%20gover