2What%20If%20Trump%20Refuses%20To%20Accept%20A%20Loss%3F%20Could%20It%20Lead%20To%20Civil%20Unrest%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERepublican%20presidential%20candidate%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20never%20been%20one%20to%20abide%20by%20rules.%20Four%20years%20ago%20he%20cried%20fraud%20and%20did%20not%20accept%20the%20presidential%20election%20result%20and%20there%20could%20be%20a%20possibility%20of%20him%20doing%20the%20same%20this%20time%20around%20after%20the%20November%205%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20the%20only%20difference%20will%20be%20that%20Trump%20will%20not%20have%20his%20presidential%20levers%20of%20power%20which%20he%20had%20in%20the%202020%20elections.%20Moreover%2C%20new%20laws%20have%20been%20implemented%20in%20the%20US%20to%20make%20it%20more%20difficult%20to%20influence%20election%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETHE%20DENIAL%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20lose%20-%20I'll%20tell%20you%20what%2C%20it's%20possible.%20Because%20they%20cheat.%20That's%20the%20only%20way%20we're%20gonna%20lose%2C%20because%20they%20cheat%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20at%20a%20Michigan%20rally%20in%20September.%20Trump's%20team%20filed%20over%2060%20lawsuits%2C%20but%20none%20of%20them%20succeeded%20in%20altering%20or%20delaying%20the%20vote%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20losing%20the%202020%20presidential%20election%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20his%20supporters%20launched%20an%20unprecedented%20effort%20to%20overturn%20the%20results.%20This%20endeavor%20involved%20spreading%20baseless%20claims%20of%20election%20fraud%20and%20rigging%20through%20the%20%26quot%3Bbig%20lie%26quot%3B%20propaganda%20technique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECIVIL%20UNREST%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Republican%20supporters%20charged%20the%20US%20Capitol%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20stop%20Mike%20Pence%20from%20confirming%20Joe%20Biden's%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20effort%20by%20Trump%20to%20suggest%20the%20election%20was%20rigged%20could%20potentially%20lead%20to%20civil%20unrest%2C%20as%20it%20did%20on%20Jan.%206%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Reuters%2C%20experts%20who%20monitor%20violent%20groups%20and%20militia%2C%20such%20as%20Peter%20Montgomery%20of%20the%20People%20For%20the%20American%20Way%2C%20a%20liberal%20think%20tank%2C%20say%20they%20are%20less%20concerned%20about%20a%20violent%20response%20from%20these%20groups%20than%20they%20are%20about%20threats%20against%20election%20workers%20counting%20votes.%20There%20also%20could%20be%20violent%20demonstrations%20in%20the%20capitals%20of%20battleground%20states%2C%20Montgomery%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Trump%20and%20his%20allies%20have%20been%20crafting%20a%20blueprint%20for%20months%20to%20cry%20if%20he%20loses%20on%20November%205th.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20November%205%20election%2C%20Republicans%20and%20Democrats%20anticipate%20a%20potentially%20lengthy%20vote-counting%20process%20that%20may%20extend%20well%20beyond%20Election%20Day%2C%20as%20mail-in%20ballots%20are%20processed%20and%20other%20votes%20are%20carefully%20verified%20and%20tallied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20it%20seems%20like%20Trump%20is%20losing%2C%20the%20delay%20in%20counting%20will%20give%20him%20a%20window%20to%20claim%20fraud%20while%20sowing%20seeds%20of%20doubt%20about%20election%20officials%20and%20although%20he%20has%20been%20threatening%20to%20put%20election%20workers%20and%20public%20workers%20behind%20bars%2C%20he%20would%20need%20to%20win%20the%20election%20first%20in%20order%20for%20that%20to%20be%20materialised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBUILD-UP%20IN%20KEY%20BATTLEGROUNDS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20anticipation%20of%20potential%20election%20controversies%2C%20Republicans%20have%20preemptively%20filed%20more%20than%20100%20lawsuits%20in%20crucial%20battleground%20states.%20These%20lawsuits%20seek%20to%20establish%20a%20basis%20for%20post-election%20challenges%2C%20including%20claims%20-%20thus%20far%20unsupported%20by%20evidence%20-%20of%20widespread%20voting%20by%20non-citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20major%20parties%20are%20gearing%20up%20to%20deploy%20thousands%20of%20trained%20volunteers%2C%20known%20as%20poll%20watchers%2C%20to%20keep%20a%20close%20eye%20on%20voting%20and%20vote%20counting%20during%20the%20upcoming%20election.%20These%20volunteers%20will%20be%20tasked%20with%20reporting%20any%20irregularities%20they%20spot.%20However%2C%20some%20voting%20rights%20advocates%20are%20sounding%20the%20alarm%2C%20worried%20that%20Republican%20poll%20watchers%20might%20disrupt%20the%20process%2C%20even%20though%20the%20Republican%20Party%20noted%20that%20the%20volunteers%20have%20been%20instructed%20to%20abide%20by%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStates%20must%20submit%20their%20election%20results%20by%20December%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20Electoral%20College%20meeting.%20Electors%20will%20then%20cast%20their%20votes%2C%20which%20are%20subsequently%20sent%20to%20Congress%20for%20formal%20verification%20in%20January%2C%20marking%20the%20final%20step%20in%20confirming%20the%20presidential%20election%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDELAYS%20AND%20MISSED%20DEADLINES%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEfforts%20to%20contest%20election%20results%2C%20fueled%20by%20Trump's%20influence%2C%20may%20cause%20certification%20delays%20and%20missed%20deadlines.%20This%20could%20provide%20grounds%20for%20Republican%20lawmakers%20to%20dispute%20the%20outcome%2C%20with%20uncertain%20legal%20consequences%20due%20to%20potentially%20biased%20judicial%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20Trump's%202020%20election%20challenges%2C%20Congress%20enacted%20reforms%20to%20prevent%20similar%20disruptions.%20The%20new%20law%20clarifies%20the%20vice%20president's%20limited%20role%2C%20prohibiting%20them%20from%20delaying%20certification%20or%20discarding%20state%20results%2C%20as%20Trump%20had%20urged%20Pence%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20measure%20also%20requires%20that%20an%20objection%20to%20a%20state's%20electoral%20count%20cannot%20be%20brought%20unless%20one-fifth%20of%20the%20members%20of%20each%20house%20of%20Congress%20agrees.%20After%20that%2C%20it%20takes%20a%20majority%20vote%20in%20each%20house%20for%20an%20objection%20to%20be%20found%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20unexpected%20outcome%20that%20enough%20electoral%20votes%20are%20tossed%20so%20that%20neither%20candidate%20reaches%20the%20majority%2C%20the%20newly%20elected%20US%20House%20of%20Representatives%20would%20choose%20the%20next%20president.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729198140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-01%2F4c4uvi68_us-capitol-650_625x300_07_January_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-if-donald-trump-refuses-to-accept-a-loss-could-it-lead-to-civil-unrest-6813362%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20has%20never%20been%20one%20to%20abide%20by%20rules.%20Four%20years%20ago%20he%20cried%20fraud%20and%20did%20not%20accept%20the%20election%20results%20and%20there%20could%20be%20a%20possibility%20of%20him%20doing%20the%20same%20this%20time%20around%20after%20the%20November%205%20election.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-if-donald-trump-refuses-to-accept-a-loss-could-it-lead-to-civil-unrest-6813362%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Starmer%20to%20travel%20to%20Germany%20for%20talks%20with%20Biden%2C%20Scholz%20and%20Macron%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729198140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F07%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-keir-starmer-joe-biden_6635828.jpg%3F20240721205335%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsir-keir-starmer-to-travel-to-germany-for-talks-with-joe-biden-olaf-scholz-and-emmanuel-macr